# Global Windsurf Rules

## 1. Design System Consistency

### Layout
- Maintain consistent max-width of 980px using Container component
- Use standardized vertical spacing (32px/2rem between sections)
- Implement responsive layouts with mobile-first approach
- Follow dark mode guidelines specific to Videos page

### Components
- Use standardized card components (ArticleCard, VideoCard, CarCard, PhotoCard)
- Maintain consistent headline styles with icons and "View All" ghost buttons
- Follow 3-column grid layout for card-based sections
- Implement hover effects and transitions consistently

## 2. Mobile Optimization
- Use list layouts on mobile where appropriate
- Implement conditional rendering for search (header vs. sticky mobile)
- Ensure proper font sizes and spacing for mobile readability
- Use responsive carousels for horizontal scrolling content

## 3. Navigation & Interaction
- Implement dropdown menus with smooth animations
- Use hover-based interactions for navigation
- Prevent event propagation in nested interactive elements
- Hide navigation elements when redundant

## 4. Visual Language
- Follow established color tokens for neutral palette and semantic colors
- Use consistent typography tokens for sizes, weights, and spacing
- Apply standardized shadow and border tokens
- Maintain brand identity with red accent colors

## 5. Content Display
- Display high-quality automotive imagery
- Use consistent aspect ratios (16:9 for media)
- Implement proper metadata display (dates, categories)
- Follow established card layout patterns

## 6. Performance & UX
- Implement proper loading states
- Use efficient search algorithms with fallbacks
- Implement proper error handling
- Use React Query for data fetching

## 7. Code Standards
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow React best practices
- Implement proper prop typing
- Use consistent naming conventions

## 8. Search Functionality
- Implement comprehensive search across all content types
- Support special case handling for car makes/models
- Use categorized search results
- Implement proper filtering and sorting

## 9. State Management
- Use appropriate React hooks
- Implement proper context usage
- Maintain consistent state updates
- Use proper cleanup in useEffect

## 10. Accessibility
- Ensure proper contrast ratios
- Implement keyboard navigation
- Use semantic HTML
- Provide proper ARIA labels